     Then, the manifold strong variational sufficient condition for problem \eqref{eq:problem-mani} under the retraction $R_{\bar{x}}$ holds  with respect to $(\bar{x}, \bar{y})$  at level $\rho > 0$ if and only if every matrix in $\overline{\nabla}_{\xi\xi}^2 l_{R_{\bar{x}}}^{\rho}(0_{\bar{x}}, \bar{y})$ is positive definite. Moreover, any $H_{\xi\xi} \in \overline{\nabla}_{\xi\xi}^2 l_{R_{\bar{x}}}^{\rho}(0_{\bar{x}}, \bar{y})$ can be written in the form
